21/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU project for Regional Economic Development presented a set of measures Monday (20 October) to promote economic growth. 
EU specialists and local authorities will implement the programme in 30 municipalities of Sarajevo district and in several other BiH settlements. 
The EU is to finance all initiatives in a bid to introduce an integrated regional approach and improve the country's business climate.
In Banja Luka meanwhile, the Republika Srpska government adopted an action plan Monday aimed at improving collection of taxes and social insurance contributions. 
The social and health insurance funds are encouraged to intensify co-operation with line ministries to prepare relevant legislative amendments. 
(Nezavisne Novine - 21/10/03; Onasa - 20/10/03)
